"🔥 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗔𝗻𝗮𝗹𝘆𝘀𝘁 𝘃𝘀. 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗦𝗰𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗶𝘀𝘁: 𝗪𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗵 𝗥𝗼𝗹𝗲 𝗙𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝗬𝗢𝗨𝗥 𝗚𝗼𝗮𝗹𝘀?\n“Should I learn Python or SQL?”\n“Do I need a PhD?”\n“Which job pays more?”\nIn my research 50+ professionals into data roles. Here’s the brutally honest breakdown (with salaries, skills, and reality checks)\n\n𝟭. 𝗖𝗼𝗿𝗲 𝗙𝗼𝗰𝘂𝘀\n✅ 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗔𝗻𝗮𝗹𝘆𝘀𝘁\nWhat: “What happened?” → Reports, dashboards, KPIs.\nTools: SQL, Excel, Tableau.\nSalary: 65K–\n65K–110K (varies by industry).\n✅ 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗦𝗰𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗶𝘀𝘁\nWhat: “What’s next?” → Predictive models, ML algorithms.\nTools: Python/R, TensorFlow, cloud platforms.\nSalary: 95K–\n95K–160K+ (FAANG roles higher)\n\n𝟮. 𝗦𝗸𝗶𝗹𝗹𝘀 𝗧𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗠𝗮𝘁𝘁𝗲𝗿\n📊 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗔𝗻𝗮𝗹𝘆𝘀𝘁\nMust-have: SQL + storytelling (turn numbers into actions).\nNice-to-have: Basic Python for automation.\nWho it fits: Detail-oriented, Excel wizards, BI lovers.\n🤖 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗦𝗰𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗶𝘀𝘁\nMust-have: Advanced Python/R + stats (p-values, regression).\nNice-to-have: Docker, Spark, A/B testing.\nWho it fits: Math nerds, experiment junkies, ML hobbyists.\n\n𝟯. 𝗖𝗮𝗿𝗲𝗲𝗿 𝗣𝗮𝘁𝗵𝘀\n🔍 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗔𝗻𝗮𝗹𝘆𝘀𝘁 →\nSenior Analyst → Analytics Manager → Director of BI.\nIndustries: Finance, Marketing, Healthcare.\n🚀 𝗗𝗮𝘁𝗮 𝗦𝗰𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗶𝘀𝘁 →\nML Engineer → AI Researcher → Chief Data Officer.\nIndustries: Tech, AI startups, IoT.\n\n𝟰. 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗛𝗮𝗿𝘀𝗵 𝗧𝗿𝘂𝘁𝗵\n⚠️ 𝗔𝗻𝗮𝗹𝘆𝘀𝘁𝘀: You’ll fight for “a seat at the table” (stakeholders ignoring insights).\n⚠️ 𝗦𝗰𝗶𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗶𝘀𝘁𝘀: You’ll battle dirty data and unrealistic CEO expectations.\n\n𝗪𝗵𝗶𝗰𝗵 𝗥𝗼𝗹𝗲 𝗦𝘂𝗶𝘁𝘀 𝗬𝗼𝘂?\nComment “A” or “S” below:\nA: “I love finding patterns in data and presenting insights.”\nS: “I want to build models that predict the future.”\n👉 Free Resource: Comment “ROADMAP” and I’ll DM you my skills checklist for both roles!\n\nPlease Tag someone who’s confused about their data career path👇.\n…more"
